004756000, "id": "2060115381147083122", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1436756712929775622/DJzC7eiy_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Robert Webber", "username": "bobwebberlawyer"}, "content": "@adrianpandev I think the best thing for laid off H-1Bs is to find a F-1 program and file to change status to F-1. \n\nThe I-539 to F-1 is eligible for premium processing (unless you are from a pause policy country). \n\nBut getting into F-1 quickly gives you a solid status versus a long pending", "parentTweet": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 0, "created": 1780002414000, "id": "2060105558032892122", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1783910473148035074/rP25AhDg_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Adrian Pandev", "username": "adrianpandev"}, "content": "The last two weeks, I have spoken to several H-1B workers who have been laid off.\n\nA lot of them don't realize the LCA adds about a week to the H-1B process. So if you are in your 60-day grace period, you don't really have 60 days. You have closer to 50.\n\nThe new employer's", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 78}, "likes": 69}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2060904525737672901", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsiTDxWX", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 97, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8650105, "raw_content": "", "author": "I-am-Orlando", "created": 1780194709050, "profile_picture": "TEnkk5XkT6JN", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "brewser724", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsiTDxWX.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/nicksortor/status/2060904525737672901?s=20", "author_flair_class":